Keen wrote:Zaphod wrote:Evidently the trailer got out a bit early, because part way through they splash "This May" on the screen. And it is a little past May 2011.So when I say to you that something is happening 'This Monday', you assume I meant yesterday? The movie's out May 2012.Until January first, that would be "next May". This May as in the May belonging to this year.If it is Tuesday, then that would be "this coming Monday", or "next Monday"...but weeks sort of blend together so it isn't likely that we would come to harsh words or traumatic amputations over it if you chose to mis-use the terms. Even calendars don't seem to completely agree; some start on Sunday, some on Monday, Hell, some on Saturday, and because of things like "payday" or whatever, people often have events and schedules in their lives which imply some other parsing of days. But here in October, "this May" is in the past. And it will stay there until the first of the year when it will magically, like a bunny playing leapfrog with a unicorn, spring ahead to the future once more.
