The idea of a "good" superhero movie now is a really tough sell for me. Unless it's a sharp anti-hero story like Watchmen or the Batmen, I just don't see how it's not already been done ... a lot. I love Joss as much as the next guy but how much can he really bring given the system? It's big time Hollywood no matter who's directing, so how different can it be if it's Joss Whedon, Michael Bay, Ridley Scott or James Cameron? No doubt he will do a commendable job of dealing with the existing mythology and advancing it in a way that is true to the tradition and history of the comics. But we're still looking at 120 minutes of explosions, right? Maybe I'm too cynical.
